AbstractService.AbstractService.name: AbstractService.AbstractService
AbstractService.AbstractService.description:
Provides base class for all API endpoints to share common infrastructure. `AbstractService` provides unified way to declare API endpoint that can
be later easily reflected to HTML or JavaScript classes. Class also provide unified logging mechanism.

By default class provides only two callback to retrieve JavaScript class and minified JavaScript class with reflected methods. Currently following 
API endpoints types are supported:

* `[GET]` - HTTP GET request processing parameters from query string
* `[POST]` - HTTP POST request processing parameters from body
* `[EVENT]` - HTTP EventSource HTML5 push mechanism callback
* `[NAVIGATE]` - HTTP GET request returning JavaScript snippet assumed to be executed on client side

In methods marked with such label arguments and return values indicates values coming in from server request and returned to server response 
instead of actual parameters/return values of method.

All Services derived from this class are available on server address `/[serviceName]` e.g. `http://localhost:8088/themeEngine` (see `Server` for more details about server 
location and configuration). All actions that can be performed on Service can be invoked either:

* directly from web browser by navigating to Service address (e.g. `http://localhost:8088/themeEngine`) and pressing Invoke/Submit button
* manually by invoking e.g. curl call for parameters (e.g. `curl --data "url=http://package.location.com/package.name.wgt" http://localhost:8088/packageRepository/installFromUrl `)

To add additional API methods use actions collection via push or splice method with object properties defined in `EndpointAction` object, e.g.

    this.actions.push({
       type: "get",
       title: "Get Data",
       endpoint: "/getData",
       callback: this.getData
     });

PackageRepositoryService.PackageReposito.name: PackageRepositoryService.PackageRepositoryService
PackageRepositoryService.PackageReposito.description:
`/packageRepository `

Manages categories and lists of available packages from remote Package Repository, installation and uninstallation of following items:

* Applications (WGT packages, see W3C Widget specification for more information)
* Themes (THM packages, see `ThemeEngine` API for more information about structure)

Fast way to install new applications is either from web browser in Package repository section or from command line by invoking e.g.

    curl --data "url=http://vendor.com/package.name" http://localhost:8088/packageRepository/install

As minimum setup there should be at least Home screen and Store applications which can be installed by calling:

    curl --data "url=http://com.intel.tizen/homescreen" http://localhost:8088/packageRepository/install
    curl --data "url=http://com.intel.tizen/store" http://localhost:8088/packageRepository/install

Service also allows silent installation of new packages or themes if both package declares that it is enabled for silent installation (`AvailablePackageData.silentInstall`) and
configuration option `PackageRepositoryOptions.doSilentInstall` is turned on.

Service downloads list of available packages each 20 seconds.

UserStatusService.UserStatusService.name: UserStatusService.UserStatusService
UserStatusService.UserStatusService.description:
`/user`

Declares User status API which provides methods to persist user status and allows user context switching. This functionality is used in cooperation
with NFC to demonstrate IVI adaptation when approached by different users using contactless method. Users are identified by cookie `iviUser` sent from
server back to NFC-enabled device.

Engine.Server.name: Engine.Server
Engine.Server.description:
Module defines server-wide options and infrastucture used by other services.

Management console for IVI engine is by default located on http://localhost:8088 and displays available API endpoints as well as installed applications. 
Main application entry point is `Home Screen` application.

All API commands can be invoked either from web browser environment (e.g. http://localhost:8088/packageRepository) or by manually (e.g. curl call). 

All API services provides encapsulation JavaScript libraries that can be used from HTML applications (e.g. http://localhost:8088/packageRepository.js). Minified version of all API services is available as well (e.g. http://localhost:8088/packageRepository.min.js).

Management console also provides `[GET] /shutdown` call which ternminates current server.

EventSourceDispatcher.EventSourceDispatc.name: EventSourceDispatcher.EventSourceDispatcher
EventSourceDispatcher.EventSourceDispatc.description:
Declares single point of dispatching HTML5 `EventSource` messages using `text/event-stream` content type to avoid WebKit limitations. 
This class works as server-side complementary component to class `ApiEndpointBase`.
WebKit engine currently supports up to 5 parallel `EventSource` sources. This can be avoided by declaring one common source and dispatching 
messages based on identificator. To send new message use emit method e.g.:

     eventSourceDispatcher.emit("send", { source: "mysource", message: "Test message" });

com.intel.tizen.coulomb.2012.AudioPlayer.description:
Represents HTML5 audio, that is utilizing Audio Service API to get/set status of currently playing song (tested with wav audio files).
Audio resources are passed to the player as an array of songs (model/playlist).
Audio player is extended by option to set buttons to control audio playback (play/pause, next, previous, shuffle, repeat), time progress bar, spectrum analyzer, info panel, volume control.
